## Setting up the project

### JavaFX

To run the project with JavaFX, you need to set up the module path correctly in IntelliJ IDEA:

1. Open **Run > Edit Configurations**.
2. Select the existing run configuration and locate the **VM Options** field.
3. Add the following option, adjusting the path to match your JavaFX SDK installation:

  --module-path "C:\path\to\javafx-sdk-23.0.1\lib" --add-modules javafx.controls,javafx.fxml

### Run without GUI

1. Open pom.xml.
2. Scroll until you see <options> in configuration.
3. Change the NoGui option to true for program to run in terminal only.
